00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:40,520
[EP6: Who Sees Whom as an Imaginary Rival?]

2
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:58,217
I think we have to talk about the performance.

3
00:02:58,217 --> 00:02:59,759
Yeah, I think that's a good idea.

4
00:02:59,759 --> 00:03:01,080
Let's talk about performance.

5
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,740
So what kind of idea do you have there?

6
00:03:08,726 --> 00:03:10,159
<i>Honey...</i>

7
00:03:10,159 --> 00:03:12,180
<i>Are you home?</i>

8
00:03:16,305 --> 00:03:17,332
Ruan Yu?

9
00:03:17,332 --> 00:03:19,240
Yeah. I'm almost home.

10
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,720
<i>Okay.</i>

11
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:24,540
<i>What? You'll meet me at the corner?</i>

12
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:27,614
[Urgent call]
<i>Okay.</i>

13
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:30,497
<i>I'll be there in five.</i>

14
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,440
<i>Someone's following you?</i>

15
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,960
Yes.

16
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,520
Don't panic.

17
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,719
Go where it's crowded and bright.

18
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,599
<i>Tell him I'm on my way.</i>

19
00:03:41,599 --> 00:03:43,819
I'm coming to you now.

20
00:03:45,684 --> 00:03:47,760
I'm almost there.

21
00:03:51,039 --> 00:03:52,240
Then...

22
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:54,960
It's okay, Lawyer Xu. I'm home now.

23
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:58,420
<i>Maybe I was overthinking.</i>

24
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:02,039
Good.

25
00:04:02,039 --> 00:04:03,666
Get some rest.

26
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:05,680
<i>About the stuff online,</i>

27
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,580
I'm handling it already.

28
00:04:09,159 --> 00:04:10,584
<i>Honey.</i>

29
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:12,919
<i>Are you home?</i>

30
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,040
I...

31
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,560
Sorry.

32
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:18,160
That call was meant for a friend.

33
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:20,599
I dialed you by mistake.

34
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:35,959
What's wrong?

35
00:04:35,959 --> 00:04:37,639
Lawyer Xu.

36
00:04:37,639 --> 00:04:38,800
I...

37
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:42,080
downstairs at my place,
there's a black van parked outside.

38
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:44,800
<i>When I was downstairs earlier, it wasn't there.</i>

39
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,859
Can you see the plate?

40
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:49,120
Not clearly.

41
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,920
But it looks like

42
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:53,400
the kind used for kidnappings.

43
00:04:58,319 --> 00:05:01,120
Usually, this isn't the kind of criminal
you're imagining.

44
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:03,800
Even if it is, they won't just break in.

45
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,560
<i>You need to do two things.</i>

46
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:07,519
First, send me your location

47
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:10,600
and the number for property management
or the security office.

48
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,600
Second, take your phone

49
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,560
and check the peephole.

50
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:16,206
Okay.

51
00:05:22,906 --> 00:05:24,582
[Tian Heng Residence]

52
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,060
I sent it.

53
00:05:29,879 --> 00:05:32,079
Don't make a sound yet.

54
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,680
<i>If you see someone suspicious</i>

55
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,520
<i>but they haven't moved yet,</i>

56
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,560
don't lock the door yet.

57
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,250
Step back from the door.

58
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:40,279
<i>Put me on speaker.</i>

59
00:05:40,279 --> 00:05:41,600
<i>Say my name out loud.</i>

60
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,203
<i>Say you're doing laundry</i>

61
00:05:43,203 --> 00:05:44,520
and want me to get the door.

62
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:46,320
Got it?

63
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,836
Got it.

64
00:05:47,836 --> 00:05:49,400
<i>If I'm done calling</i>

65
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:51,226
and they still don't leave,

66
00:05:51,226 --> 00:05:52,720
lock the door fast

67
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,780
and call the police.

68
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:07,533
<i>What's wrong?</i>

69
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,873
Hello?

70
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,000
<i>Hello.</i>

71
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,640
<i>The number you dialed is powered off.</i>

72
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:21,709
Ruan Yu,

73
00:06:21,709 --> 00:06:24,109
are you home?

74
00:06:40,279 --> 00:06:42,419
It's me, Li Shi Can.

75
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:47,120
Shi Can? What are you doing here?

76
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,240
Didn't we say

77
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:50,760
to see at the usual place?

78
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:53,640
Didn't you call me because of the livestream?

79
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,840
You knew I was livestreaming?

80
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,293
Ming Ying and I were free at home that day,

81
00:06:58,293 --> 00:07:00,400
so we watched your livestream.

82
00:07:01,042 --> 00:07:03,720
You actually quite care about me.

83
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:05,680
Can I come in first?

84
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,199
I'm a little...

85
00:07:07,199 --> 00:07:09,140
Sure. Come in.

86
00:07:14,675 --> 00:07:15,680
Shi Can.

87
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,160
I don't have men's slippers.

88
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,223
Just keep your shoes on.

89
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,508
Still no boyfriend?

90
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:29,306
Before showbiz, you weren't this gossipy.

91
00:07:32,399 --> 00:07:33,519
Have a seat.

92
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:34,919
Okay.

93
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:40,640
Then I'll...

94
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,326
Sure, go ahead.

95
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:52,120
Other people's gossip, I really don't care.

96
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,705
But you're different.

97
00:07:53,705 --> 00:07:56,100
You're my...

98
00:07:57,759 --> 00:08:00,480
closest senior.

99
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,937
So you do know I'm your senior.

100
00:08:01,937 --> 00:08:03,779
Yet you didn't call me that just now.

101
00:08:03,779 --> 00:08:05,280
My bad.

102
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:07,820
This is my apology.

103
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,120
I saw it on the way,

104
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,839
so I grabbed one for you.

105
00:08:13,839 --> 00:08:16,265
Isn't this from that tea shop
by the college town?

106
00:08:16,265 --> 00:08:18,573
- That place is still open?
- Yes.

107
00:08:20,275 --> 00:08:21,313
Here.

108
00:08:21,313 --> 00:08:22,713
Thanks.

109
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:26,120
Red and mung bean milk tea.

110
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,760
Full sugar, no tea base.

111
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,120
Swap the milk for soy milk.

112
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:31,500
Red beans only, no mung beans.

113
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:36,519
Back when I ran errands

114
00:08:36,519 --> 00:08:38,399
for you seniors, I kept notes.

115
00:08:38,399 --> 00:08:40,840
The names are gone now, though.

116
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,200
Good thing I remembered right.

117
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:45,000
Or I'd be even more guilty.

118
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,120
That's thoughtful of you.

119
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:49,453
But I don't have much to offer.

120
00:08:49,453 --> 00:08:51,416
May I get you a cup of warm water?

121
00:08:51,416 --> 00:08:53,279
Sure. Warm water's fine.

122
00:08:53,279 --> 00:08:55,280
I'm resting my voice lately, so less drink.

123
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:57,093
Okay, hang on.

124
00:09:05,893 --> 00:09:07,480
Here.

125
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:09,133
Thanks.

126
00:09:13,362 --> 00:09:14,920
By the way, Shi Can,

127
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:17,440
is that car downstairs yours?

128
00:09:18,799 --> 00:09:19,960
Yeah, it's mine.

129
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,960
It's kind of messy.

130
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,720
It rained on the way from Su City.

131
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,980
Got dirty from the road.

132
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:29,000
You came all the way from Su City?

133
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:31,720
You could've just told me
you were here for work.

134
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,653
Of course, not just for work.

135
00:09:33,653 --> 00:09:35,033
I already wanted to see you.

136
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:38,126
The stream just gave me a reason to call.

137
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,404
There's something

138
00:09:43,404 --> 00:09:45,000
I had to apologize for

139
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,659
in person.

140
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,480
Shi Can, give me a second.

141
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,919
I need to deal with something.

142
00:09:51,919 --> 00:09:53,573
Okay.

143
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:57,973
[xhs invites you to a video call]

144
00:10:07,879 --> 00:10:09,760
Lawyer Xu, I'm really sorry.

145
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,000
My phone died just now,

146
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,120
so I couldn't let you know I was safe.

147
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,900
Sorry.

148
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,553
A friend came over.

149
00:10:24,095 --> 00:10:26,559
<i>While you were staring at Li Shi Can,</i>

150
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:30,564
<i>you were reminiscing about Xu someone, right?</i>

151
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:34,400
Lawyer Xu?

152
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,813
Yes.

153
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:38,919
Hello.

154
00:10:38,919 --> 00:10:40,500
Sorry.

155
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:43,480
Don't report to me.

156
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:45,948
Tell the police instead.

157
00:10:45,948 --> 00:10:48,273
[Call duration: 3:20]
<i>The police?</i>

158
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,960
He's your lawyer?

159
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,540
Yeah.

160
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,012
I need to take this.

161
00:11:07,748 --> 00:11:08,840
Hello?

162
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,960
<i>Can, the police got me downstairs.</i>

163
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:12,793
<i>Come help me!</i>

164
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:21,879
Give me a moment, both of you.

165
00:11:21,879 --> 00:11:23,685
Thanks.

166
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:28,325
Let's wait over there.

167
00:11:28,325 --> 00:11:30,140
Yes.

168
00:11:32,399 --> 00:11:34,240
I'm really sorry, Shi Can.

169
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,559
I overthought it.

170
00:11:35,559 --> 00:11:38,200
I'm so sorry that
I dragged you and your innocent friend

171
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,876
into this incident.

172
00:11:39,876 --> 00:11:41,399
I should be the one apologizing.

173
00:11:41,399 --> 00:11:44,620
I didn't handle things well with Cen Si Si.

174
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:54,760
Cen Si Si told me

175
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:56,680
you two are childhood friends.

176
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,039
I'm from Su City.

177
00:11:58,039 --> 00:11:59,399
She's from Hang City.

178
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:01,480
How would we be childhood friends?

179
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:03,520
Back then,
her dad came to Su City for business.

180
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,337
She transferred there with him.

181
00:12:05,337 --> 00:12:07,080
We were classmates for two years.

182
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,960
Then we went to the same college.

183
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:12,840
Maybe to her, that counts as

184
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,500
half a childhood friend?

185
00:12:16,559 --> 00:12:19,640
And all these years, she's had feelings

186
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:21,920
for me.

187
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:23,480
I have an alt Weibo account.

188
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,639
I followed your account, Wen Xiang.

189
00:12:25,639 --> 00:12:27,840
She tracked you down from that.

190
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:31,419
So she probably got the wrong idea.

191
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:39,700
Then how did you know I was Wen Xiang?

192
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:43,360
Back in college,
you asked me to fix your computer.

193
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,560
Remember?

194
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:47,399
One of your files had that pen name on it.

195
00:12:47,399 --> 00:12:49,080
I remembered it

196
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:51,140
and followed you quietly.

197
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:57,120
You've really stayed hidden all these years.

198
00:12:57,901 --> 00:13:00,000
I figured you creators

199
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,480
like to keep online

200
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,880
and real life separate.

201
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:04,639
Otherwise, it's like running naked online.

202
00:13:04,639 --> 00:13:06,400
What's the difference?

203
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:07,560
But don't worry.

204
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:09,470
I don't snoop on you.

205
00:13:09,470 --> 00:13:12,040
Otherwise I wouldn't have only found out
after coming back home.

206
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:13,279
If I'd known sooner,

207
00:13:13,279 --> 00:13:15,140
I'd have dealt with it already.

208
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,000
Someone was deleting comments for me on Weibo,

209
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,559
and someone also leaked Cen Si Si's identity.

210
00:13:21,559 --> 00:13:24,320
Was that your PR team?

211
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:26,160
I only told them to moderate comments.

212
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:28,679
As for the information leak...

213
00:13:28,679 --> 00:13:30,419
it wasn't me.

214
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,880
Maybe netizens did it

215
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:35,280
on their own?

216
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,044
Is that so?

217
00:13:39,279 --> 00:13:41,000
Either way, I dragged you into this.

218
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,679
I'll clean it up.

219
00:13:42,679 --> 00:13:44,240
Things have died down now.

220
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,960
You just focus on the case.

221
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:48,286
Leave the rest to me.

222
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,440
No need.

223
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:52,200
None of this was your fault.

224
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,200
And you're busy enough already.

225
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,640
Don't worry about this.

226
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:58,240
I have lawyers helping me.

227
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:03,919
Right. I saw the signature

228
00:14:03,919 --> 00:14:05,600
on your legal statement

229
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:06,880
was Zhikun Law Firm.

230
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:09,159
Lawyer Xu

231
00:14:09,159 --> 00:14:11,440
works at Zhikun Law Firm?

232
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:12,519
Yes.

233
00:14:12,519 --> 00:14:15,740
I-Is he any good?

234
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:18,320
Don't worry. He's very professional

235
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,899
and very experienced.

236
00:14:25,564 --> 00:14:29,607
[Xu Huai Song from Su City No.1 High School]

237
00:14:44,919 --> 00:14:46,933
Found you at last.

238
00:14:47,559 --> 00:14:49,100
Xu someone.

239
00:14:50,182 --> 00:14:53,682
But looks like you found her, too.

240
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:44,900
[2016 Midsummer Night's Dream Art Performance]

241
00:16:09,887 --> 00:16:12,320
So, did you find

242
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:14,380
your Hua Ze Lei?

243
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,360
<i>Lawyer Xu.</i>

244
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,880
<i>I'm really sorry about today.</i>

245
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,840
<i>I made you worry for nothing.</i>

246
00:16:55,399 --> 00:16:56,920
<i>Lawyer Xu.</i>

247
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:58,960
<i>Did you read the file?</i>

248
00:17:04,095 --> 00:17:06,580
Not even one reply.

249
00:17:10,039 --> 00:17:12,280
Then again...

250
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:14,960
Got played like this
and reported to the police...

251
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:16,780
anyone could be annoyed.

252
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,566
Besides,

253
00:17:21,566 --> 00:17:23,905
he's busy to begin with.

254
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:28,860
Or maybe he never saw it at all?

255
00:17:38,340 --> 00:17:39,440
<i>Lawyer Xu.</i>

256
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:41,799
<i>Have you been busy these past two days?</i>

257
00:17:41,799 --> 00:17:45,179
<i>When can we go further into the case?</i>

258
00:17:57,286 --> 00:17:59,246
<i>In ten minutes.</i>

259
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:03,650
<i>Then I'll turn on my laptop.</i>

260
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,640
<i>No need. In ten minutes,</i>

261
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:08,300
<i>downstairs at your place.</i>

262
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:32,334
You don't have to rush over.

263
00:18:32,334 --> 00:18:35,120
Sorry, Lawyer Xu. Kept you waiting.

264
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,720
<i>Because of that stupid mix-up,</i>

265
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:38,680
<i>that high-up Mr. Xu ignored me
for two whole days.</i>

266
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,160
<i>Not even a comma.</i>

267
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:44,019
<i>How could I make someone like you
wait even one more second?</i>

268
00:18:45,039 --> 00:18:46,129
Get in.

269
00:18:46,129 --> 00:18:48,086
We're going to the firm.

270
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:06,800
Lawyer Xu.

271
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:09,640
What are you doing near my place?

272
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:12,440
I am passing by on the way
from the airport to the firm.

273
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:15,826
<i>The airport to the firm passing by here?</i>

274
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:21,565
Thanks for picking me up.

275
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:30,320
Hello?

276
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:31,986
Ms. Zhang.

277
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:35,054
Okay, got it.

278
00:19:35,692 --> 00:19:36,760
Lawyer Xu.

279
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:39,320
Ms. Zhang is handling a case at the site
and something came up.

280
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:41,840
I may need to go over.

281
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:44,361
Then when you're done,
take my luggage to the apartment.

282
00:19:44,361 --> 00:19:45,761
Okay.

283
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:31,660
Why not get a cab?

284
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:51,200
Want to talk at my place?

285
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,799
If it's not a good time, next time.

286
00:20:52,799 --> 00:20:53,920
I'll head back to the office first.

287
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:56,300
No, it's fine. This way.

288
00:21:04,279 --> 00:21:05,900
Watch your step.

289
00:21:13,759 --> 00:21:16,359
<i>He's only mad at you for two days.</i>

290
00:21:16,359 --> 00:21:18,820
<i>Look how hard you're sucking up.</i>

291
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:30,500
<i>Oh no.</i>

292
00:21:31,359 --> 00:21:32,820
What is it?

293
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:36,000
Nothing, Lawyer Xu.

294
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,939
Please wait a moment.

295
00:22:05,450 --> 00:22:07,456
Lawyer Xu, come in.

296
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:21,519
Sorry.

297
00:22:21,519 --> 00:22:23,240
I don't have men's slippers.

298
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:25,380
Just keep your shoes on.

299
00:22:41,520 --> 00:22:44,420
That was where I sat for video calls before.

300
00:22:48,119 --> 00:22:50,140
<i>My friend came over.</i>

301
00:22:55,792 --> 00:22:57,375
Yes.

302
00:22:58,516 --> 00:22:59,569
Lawyer Xu.

303
00:22:59,569 --> 00:23:01,359
Want something to drink?

304
00:23:01,359 --> 00:23:02,680
Coffee is fine.

305
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:04,520
Instant okay?

306
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:05,600
Yes.

307
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:07,900
Sure. Have a seat.

308
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:34,160
<i>I was only thinking not to make
the big shot come for nothing...</i>

309
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:35,799
<i>and forgot the time difference.</i>

310
00:23:35,799 --> 00:23:37,939
<i>I should've let him back to sleep.</i>

311
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:36,580
Xu...

312
00:27:00,319 --> 00:27:01,519
Sorry.

313
00:27:01,519 --> 00:27:03,240
I dozed off.

314
00:27:07,673 --> 00:27:09,315
Hello?

315
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:12,500
I just fell asleep.

316
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:15,453
Haven't eaten yet.

317
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:17,906
Bye.

318
00:27:23,079 --> 00:27:25,799
Lawyer Xu, you haven't eaten?

319
00:27:27,773 --> 00:27:30,473
Want to grab a bite first?

320
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:37,386
It's too hot outside.

321
00:27:40,244 --> 00:27:42,265
Then let's order takeout.

322
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:45,934
Oh, you don't eat takeout.

323
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,629
How about...

324
00:27:52,629 --> 00:27:54,839
I cook you something?

325
00:27:54,839 --> 00:27:56,080
I have food at home.

326
00:27:56,080 --> 00:27:59,240
See if anything works.

327
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:04,120
If it's not too much trouble.

328
00:28:04,120 --> 00:28:05,279
Not at all.

329
00:28:05,279 --> 00:28:08,100
Come check the kitchen. See what you want.

330
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,119
With what's here,

331
00:28:15,119 --> 00:28:17,404
I can make sandwiches or pasta.

332
00:28:17,404 --> 00:28:19,693
Pick what you want.

333
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,380
This one.

334
00:28:25,559 --> 00:28:28,380
Looks like your stomach
isn't fully westernized yet.

335
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:32,200
How do you want it cooked?

336
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:34,006
Fried.

337
00:28:34,006 --> 00:28:36,560
Then go sit in the living room.

338
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:48,780
<i>Milled rice cake isn't great fried.</i>

339
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:50,599
<i>He probably wants</i>

340
00:28:50,599 --> 00:28:52,820
<i>Su City's lard rice cake.</i>

341
00:29:09,599 --> 00:29:10,759
Lawyer Xu.

342
00:29:10,759 --> 00:29:12,920
I switched it to Su City lard rice cake.

343
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:15,820
You've been abroad,
so you probably don't get this much.

344
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:17,840
Thanks.

345
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:28,799
How did you know

346
00:29:28,799 --> 00:29:30,806
I'm from Su City?

347
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:35,720
I looked you up.

348
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:38,401
There are articles about you online.

349
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:42,540
Why look into me?

350
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:47,440
Just...

351
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:50,200
basic background on my counsel.

352
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:53,459
I also know Lawyer Liu is from Hang City.

353
00:29:58,400 --> 00:29:59,600
Lawyer Xu.

354
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:01,599
Eat it while it's hot.

355
00:30:01,599 --> 00:30:02,999
Okay.

356
00:30:15,519 --> 00:30:17,079
<i>You're eating so politely.</i>

357
00:30:17,079 --> 00:30:19,740
<i>So is it good or not?</i>

358
00:30:30,396 --> 00:30:32,080
You want some?

359
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:34,079
I don't.

360
00:30:34,079 --> 00:30:36,000
Lawyer Xu, go ahead.

361
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:38,219
I'll wash the dishes.

362
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:02,960
<i>Your appetite isn't very polite though.</i>

363
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:05,499
<i>Guess I fried it well today.</i>

364
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:09,222
Lawyer Xu. You done eating?

365
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:16,620
I still haven't checked.

366
00:31:17,359 --> 00:31:20,080
Busy these past few days?

367
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:21,813
Yes.

368
00:31:21,813 --> 00:31:23,473
Didn't even check WeChat.

369
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:30,400
<i>So you weren't ignoring me on purpose.</i>

370
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:33,753
<i>I knew it. You're not that petty.</i>

371
00:31:51,286 --> 00:31:53,426
Hello? What is it?

372
00:31:58,168 --> 00:32:02,093
I put the cat food
in the lower kitchen cabinet.

373
00:32:02,093 --> 00:32:03,706
Yeah.

374
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:08,579
Handle it.

375
00:32:10,519 --> 00:32:12,559
<i>First, he has a cat.</i>

376
00:32:12,559 --> 00:32:14,680
<i>Second, he doesn't know how to bathe it.</i>

377
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:17,460
<i>So, who usually bathes the cat?</i>

378
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:20,300
<i>You mean</i>

379
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:23,219
<i>someone else lives with him?</i>

380
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:26,060
<i>His girlfriend?</i>

381
00:32:27,241 --> 00:32:29,799
<i>Maybe he usually takes it to a pet shop.</i>

382
00:32:29,799 --> 00:32:32,433
<i>But possibly you're right.</i>

383
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:41,080
Ruan Yu.

384
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:43,891
I need some sleep.

385
00:32:54,559 --> 00:32:56,179
Lawyer Xu.

386
00:32:57,040 --> 00:32:59,560
You're sleeping here?

387
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:01,380
Or maybe I should...

388
00:33:04,079 --> 00:33:05,580
Xu...

389
00:33:14,279 --> 00:33:16,979
Out that fast.

390
00:33:32,686 --> 00:33:33,840
Being a lawyer

391
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:36,800
really drains you.

392
00:34:32,040 --> 00:34:34,480
[Yet reality was always cruel.
He Shi Qian seemed not to notice...]

393
00:35:02,552 --> 00:35:05,235
[I'm leaving]

394
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:44,559
Counselor Xu.

395
00:35:44,559 --> 00:35:47,880
You've been showing up pretty rarely lately.

396
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:49,080
Feels like the last time

397
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:51,276
was half a month ago.

398
00:35:51,276 --> 00:35:52,826
Yes.

399
00:35:53,599 --> 00:35:54,957
Want a tea egg? My treat.

400
00:35:54,957 --> 00:35:56,079
No.

401
00:35:56,079 --> 00:35:57,119
I ate too much last night.

402
00:35:57,119 --> 00:35:58,400
Still digesting it.

403
00:35:58,400 --> 00:36:00,920
What did you eat that you're still full?

404
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:02,899
Fried lard rice cake.

405
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:05,599
That's a pretty nice life.

406
00:36:05,599 --> 00:36:08,393
Well, it's a Su City specialty.

407
00:36:09,079 --> 00:36:10,760
Fried rice cake for yourself?

408
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:12,039
Not bad.

409
00:36:12,039 --> 00:36:14,220
Wasn't me, actually.

410
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:23,019
Oh, there's a story.

411
00:36:23,679 --> 00:36:25,320
Ruan Yu made it for me.

412
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:26,440
Who?

413
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:27,480
Ruan Yu.

414
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:30,560
Why did she fry rice cake for you?
What's going on with you two?

415
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:34,653
A client making rice cake
for her lawyer is weird?

416
00:36:34,653 --> 00:36:36,320
Isn't it? Forget client and lawyer.

417
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:38,160
What kind of client makes food for a lawyer?

418
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:40,000
Depends on the client,

419
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,000
and the lawyer too.

420
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:42,280
What kind?

421
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:45,260
At least not some lovestruck lawyer.

422
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:50,026
Being likable is a gift.

423
00:36:56,645 --> 00:36:57,691
Take your bag.

424
00:36:57,691 --> 00:36:59,400
Time for work.

425
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:01,160
Did you just roast me?

426
00:37:01,160 --> 00:37:03,432
But I can't prove it.

427
00:37:23,199 --> 00:37:25,119
<i>When's the update coming?</i>

428
00:37:25,119 --> 00:37:26,599
<i>My comfort read!</i>

429
00:37:26,599 --> 00:37:28,700
<i>Come back already!</i>

430
00:37:30,480 --> 00:37:33,400
<i>Every writer gets stuck.</i>

431
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:35,519
<i>This time's different.</i>

432
00:37:35,519 --> 00:37:38,039
<i>The hero is right there.</i>

433
00:37:38,039 --> 00:37:41,019
<i>How could I keep writing like nothing happened?</i>

434
00:37:42,680 --> 00:37:44,880
<i>I believe the author is innocent now.</i>

435
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:47,000
<i>Now I'm just wondering</i>

436
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:48,840
<i>if it's her real story.</i>

437
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:50,400
<i>Same here.</i>

438
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:51,519
<i>This blew up so much,</i>

439
00:37:51,519 --> 00:37:53,800
<i>does the real-life hero know yet?</i>

440
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:56,997
[Let's meet by
Counter-Plagiarism Comparison Chart]

441
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:06,639
Anyone still working this late

442
00:38:06,639 --> 00:38:09,260
is this city's elite.

443
00:38:12,179 --> 00:38:13,240
<i>Lawyer Xu.</i>

444
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:14,520
<i>I got your email.</i>

445
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:16,080
<i>You're still working on my case this late.</i>

446
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:18,160
<i>Thanks.</i>

447
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:20,360
<i>Jet lag, that's all.</i>

448
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,199
<i>If you're still up,</i>

449
00:38:24,199 --> 00:38:26,480
<i>let's talk about the case.</i>

450
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:28,360
<i>Okay. Video?</i>

451
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:29,760
<i>Voice call.</i>

452
00:38:47,398 --> 00:38:48,599
Lawyer Xu.

453
00:38:48,599 --> 00:38:49,960
Sorry, one moment.

454
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:51,520
I'm going downstairs for a file.

455
00:38:51,520 --> 00:38:52,980
Okay.

456
00:39:03,038 --> 00:39:04,440
Lawyer Xu.

457
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:06,840
Yes. I'm here.

458
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:13,360
<i>Is it raining there?</i>

459
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:16,079
It is.

460
00:39:16,079 --> 00:39:17,320
Then I guess

461
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:19,680
<i>we're under the same cloud.</i>

462
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:36,639
Lawyer Xu, I'm back.

463
00:39:36,639 --> 00:39:38,480
Okay.

464
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:40,239
Then...

465
00:39:40,239 --> 00:39:42,619
let's start with paragraph 3.

466
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:44,979
<i>In this part,</i>

467
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:49,320
the heroine is scared of thunder

468
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:51,680
and stuck in the gallery by rain.

469
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:54,680
She hears him playing piano

470
00:39:54,680 --> 00:39:57,000
and feels comforted.

471
00:39:57,640 --> 00:40:00,079
<i>In the other novel, that's not there.</i>

472
00:40:00,079 --> 00:40:02,240
So should we point it out?

473
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:03,880
In the two novels,

474
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:06,960
the piano room descriptions are pretty similar.

475
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:09,119
Piano rooms probably all look alike.

476
00:40:09,119 --> 00:40:10,900
Did you forget?

477
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:14,200
Forget what?

478
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:23,039
Did you forget to switch to Wi-Fi?

479
00:40:23,039 --> 00:40:26,419
<i>Your signal sounds bad.
I can't hear you clearly.</i>

480
00:40:32,200 --> 00:40:34,019
I switched it already.

481
00:40:35,499 --> 00:40:36,601
Better now.

482
00:40:36,601 --> 00:40:37,840
I can hear you now.

483
00:40:37,840 --> 00:40:40,260
Okay, let's continue.

484
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:42,880
In the next part,

485
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:44,760
the heroine once turned down

486
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:47,040
a clingy male classmate in public.

487
00:40:47,040 --> 00:40:49,680
She told him not to mess with her studies.

488
00:40:49,680 --> 00:40:52,079
And that's exactly why after seeing that,

489
00:40:52,079 --> 00:40:53,760
the hero didn't want

490
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:56,496
to affect her studies, so he never confessed.

491
00:40:56,496 --> 00:40:57,736
<i>Right.</i>

492
00:40:57,736 --> 00:40:59,800
From what I saw, in the Poet's posts,

493
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:02,293
it still doesn't explain
why he never confessed.

494
00:41:02,293 --> 00:41:04,519
This part shouldn't overlap, right?

495
00:41:04,519 --> 00:41:05,960
But this setup

496
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:07,860
feels a little weak.

497
00:41:09,080 --> 00:41:11,380
<i>A little weak?</i>

498
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:14,440
But for high schoolers,

499
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:16,559
studying is the biggest thing.

500
00:41:16,559 --> 00:41:18,133
Besides that,

501
00:41:18,133 --> 00:41:20,740
what other reason would he have not to confess?

502
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:25,720
Not every high schooler

503
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:27,579
is that lucky.

504
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:34,260
I was being too absolute.

505
00:41:39,032 --> 00:41:41,360
Then this setup

506
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:43,700
won't hurt the case, right?

507
00:41:45,336 --> 00:41:47,686
It's okay. I'm just reminding you.

508
00:41:48,372 --> 00:41:51,480
The novel still has to be updated, right?

509
00:41:51,480 --> 00:41:53,079
So sort it out early

510
00:41:53,079 --> 00:41:54,320
and start posting again.

511
00:41:54,320 --> 00:41:57,139
That way public opinion can turn your way.

512
00:41:58,320 --> 00:41:59,900
Yeah.

513
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:17,260
The rain stopped.

514
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:39,119
<i>It rained so hard.</i>

515
00:42:39,119 --> 00:42:41,700
<i>If I'd known,
I wouldn't have come feed the cat.</i>

516
00:43:03,280 --> 00:43:05,019
<i>Is it him?</i>

517
00:43:54,313 --> 00:43:56,008
<i>Xu Huai Song.</i>

518
00:43:56,008 --> 00:43:59,053
<i>That bright, clean boyish glow in you</i>

519
00:43:59,053 --> 00:44:01,199
<i>lit up all</i>

520
00:44:01,199 --> 00:44:02,920
<i>all my rainy seasons,</i>

521
00:44:02,920 --> 00:44:04,979
<i>in my girlhood.</i>

522
00:44:48,880 --> 00:44:50,880
<i>Hello, Dad.</i>

523
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:52,979
<i>Okay, I'm heading out now.</i>

524
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:06,221
The rain stopped here, too.

525
00:45:06,832 --> 00:45:08,611
Then let's keep going.

526
00:45:09,960 --> 00:45:11,360
Okay.

527
00:45:57,960 --> 00:45:59,360
Ruan Yu.

528
00:46:38,239 --> 00:46:39,760
<i>What is it?</i>

529
00:46:39,760 --> 00:46:41,640
Lawyer Xu, sorry.

530
00:46:41,640 --> 00:46:44,400
I accidentally fell asleep last night.

531
00:46:45,160 --> 00:46:47,559
Why didn't you hang up?

532
00:46:47,559 --> 00:46:50,619
<i>I think I was asleep too.</i>

533
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:56,200
Then...

534
00:46:57,680 --> 00:46:59,701
I'll hang up first.

535
00:47:04,039 --> 00:47:06,519
What was that?

536
00:47:06,519 --> 00:47:08,336
<i>An ambulance.</i>

537
00:47:09,679 --> 00:47:11,840
Why is there an ambulance?

538
00:47:11,840 --> 00:47:14,602
<i>I'm at the hospital.</i>

